    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "FK",
    "text": "--was taken, I would say, in summer of 1944, a few weeks after I escaped from Treblinka. And this picture shows a few survivors, including this lady to the left. Her name was [NON-ENGLISH]. She was in Treblinka. And the lady below that, sitting, we called her [NON-ENGLISH]. She-- also, she worked in the laundry in Treblinka. And that other young lady, she survived outside the camp. Next to her, that's myself. And to the left, you've got Mr. Weitzman. He also was in Treblinka, but subsequently died. And the other individual is a Russian soldier, a Jewish Russian soldier, by the name of [NON-ENGLISH]. [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] The picture that you're looking at here is when I was inducted into the Polish army in November of 1944. And--",
