    "tag": "FK",
    "text": "And my name at the time, obviously, was Manfred Kort. This, again, this is me, Fred Kort. This picture was taken about a year and a half ago when I was appointed ambassador to the Tel Aviv Foundation. So when I say a year and a half ago, so that would have been in 1993, late 1993. [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] This picture was taken less than a year ago. It was on the 23rd of July, 1994, which was exactly to the day 50 years of my escape from Treblinka. So it would have been the 23rd, if I didn't say it, 23rd of July. And what you  are looking at here-- is a picture of all 15 Korts that are now here, that live here in Los Angeles. Starting with the left, which is my youngest son, David, then comes his wife, Kathy. Then comes my oldest son, Jordan and his youngest-- no, and his girl.",
